cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a novel architecture for improving the efficiency and performance of convolutional networks in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques and optimization strategies, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the proposed architecture involves modeling relationships between channels, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
